Brettenwald wrote:I feel like it's important for the "effortposter" community to remember their roots. (Full disclosure: I do not consider myself one since I generally stay off F7 anyway, but I run a Discord server with a lot of people who like this board so I know what I'm talking about.) You do have people like Texkentuck, ZN, Free Ravensburg, etc.; the kind of posters where you have to ask yourself "why are these people even here" who make up let's say 50% of the population, and you've got the kind that post three times before getting bored and leaving that's about 20%. In the 30% that's left, you have committed posters like ValZ, Synne, Foehn, Wormfodder, Hyrule, Las Palmeras/TSP, Kiu Ghesik, Batavia, Tsaivao and many others who occupy a beloved niche in the community and are a reliable source of fantastic content. The problem, in my opinion, is that there are some people among us who see that collective 50% as uniformly irredeemable and forever destined to be shit. This is a valid position though only mostly true. I say "mostly true" because occasionally you can find users like Langenia who were accepted by the community, got some mentorship, and got a lot better at RPing. That's what we need to do: find users with potential and help them use it effectively. We were all noobs once, so ask yourself if you'd want to be shit on by a community you genuinely wanted to be a part of.
Gandoor wrote:Really at the end of the day the biggest problem is that people just take this game way too seriously.

This is an extremely basic and satirical web game based on some Aussie dude's (honestly not that good) political satire novel that just happened to gain an audience of fuckin losers people interested in politics, nation building, etc. because the basic nature of the gameplay itself meant that they could develop their nations as they wanted on the discussion forums.

It ain't that serious folks.

This is also an important thing to remember. It's just a game, my dudes/dudettes/spiritually dudelike nonbinary entities. We're just here to have fun and share our brainrot with other creative types. Why be such a spoilsport?

TL;DR take a chill pill and be kind to one another.

Personally I don't really mind wank-nations that much. Sure, make your nation a real life country but stronk, whatever, I don't care. My real problem with these kind of nations is that the geopolitical situation can be pretty boring in them. External opposition meanwhile seems to be completely steamrolled in a war that the wanked nation easily won. I mean for crying out loud, give your nation an actual challenge to overcome. Hell, have aliens invade your planet, I don't care, just create an interesting conflict that is an actual challenge for your nations, because otherwise your setting becomes pretty boring.
